data.description: Come in to this welcoming ranch-style home that offers both affordability and comfort. As you come inside, you'll immediately feel at ease in the charming yet open main living area, where vaulted ceilings add a touch of spaciousness and airiness to the living space.  The layout is simple and functional, providing distinct spaces for living, dining, and relaxing.It's the perfect canvas for creating a homey atmosphere that's ideal for everyday living and casual get-togethers with friends and family.  Find solace in the owner's suite, accessed through double doors that add a touch of charm to the space (and ease to move furniture in and out). Here, you'll have your own private retreat where you can unwind and recharge after a long day.  Outside, nature beckons with nearby trails waiting to be explored, offering a refreshing escape from the hustle and bustle of daily life.   Plus, the convenience of having a gas station and amenities nearby (Seldon and Wasilla Fishhook) ensures that you'll have the essentials close at hand and also that you do not have to go to 'town' if you do not want to.  One of the highlights of this home is the greenbelt behind the property, providing a sense of privacy and tranquility that's hard to come by at this price point. It's the perfect backdrop for enjoying peaceful moments in your own backyard, surrounded by the beauty of nature.  And when it's time to venture out, easy access to E Seldon Rd offers a convenient route to Palmer or Anchorage, making your daily commute a breeze. Just think! You can avoid the commuting traffic coming into Wasilla by using Seldon Extension. You can also sneak into Wasilla via Wasilla Fishhook and avoid highways.   Memory Lake public access is just off Hebrides. The lake is stocked  annually and has Arctic Char, Chinook Salmon, Rainbow Trout (not stocked) and Northern Pike.  Sorry, the playset does not stay with the home.  Washer and dryer do not stay with home.
